            "title": "Question 1",
            "id": 75856,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What's the keyword that decides if a code block should run or not?</p><selection multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\"><code>if</code></item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\"><code>when</code></item><item value=\"3\" correct=\"false\"><code>for</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>if</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Example 5",
            "id": 75894,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Code the variable that displays <code>\"Take an umbrella\"</code> in the console.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"is_rainy = \" /><text value=\"True\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"is_sunny = \" /><text value=\"False\" class=\"literal\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"if\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" is_rainy:\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Take an umbrella&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"36\" endIndex=\"44\" /><option correct=\"false\"><content><text value=\"is_sunny\" /></content></option></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"Take an umbrella\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick <code>is_rainy</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question 6",
            "id": 75863,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What kind of value do we use as a condition for an if statement?</p><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">Boolean</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">String</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">Number</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Make sure to pick Boolean.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question 5",
            "id": 75864,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Based on indentation, when will <code>print(\"Starting game ...\")</code> run?</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"python\" name=\"script.py\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"character = \" /><text value=\"&quot;Wizard&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\";\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"if\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" character == \" /><text value=\"&quot;Knight&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\": \" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Weapon: sword&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"print(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Starting game ...&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\")\" /></content></code><selection iscode=\"false\" multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">Always, regardless of whether the <code>if</code> block runs, as it's indented at the same level</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">Only when the <code>if</code> block runs</item><item value=\"3\" correct=\"false\">Never, because this code gives an <code>IndentationError</code></item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Always, regardless of whether the <code>if</code> block runs, as it's indented at the same level.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Question 4",
            "id": 75858,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>What do we call statements that run or skip code depending on a condition being <code>True</code> or <code>False</code>?</p><selection multiple=\"multiple\"><item value=\"1\" correct=\"true\">If statements</item><item value=\"2\" correct=\"false\">Else statements</item><item value=\"3\" correct=\"false\">For loops</item></selection><p visible-if=\"wrong\">If statements.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
